{"title":"Wolf Tooth LoneWolf Aero Chainguide corrals your 1x setup","link":"https://bikerumor.com/wolf-tooth-lonewolf-aero-chainguide-corrals-your-1x-setup/","date":1687623079000,"content":"<p>The new Wolf Tooth Components LoneWolf Aero Chainguide has been tested by pro road team Jumbo-Visma (at Roubaix, Giro, and will be raced at Le Tour, too) and at this year’s Unbound, which had a rough muddy start.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It uses a machined alloy body with replaceable plastic guide that sits close enough to the chain to prevent it from bouncing off, negating the need for a full shroud.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Wolf-Tooth-LoneWolf-Aero-Chainguide-3.jpg\"><img width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Wolf-Tooth-LoneWolf-Aero-Chainguide-3.jpg\" alt=\"wolf tooth components LoneWolf aero chain guide for road and gravel bikes shown from side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Wolf-Tooth-LoneWolf-Aero-Chainguide-3.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Wolf-Tooth-LoneWolf-Aero-Chainguide-3-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Wolf-Tooth-LoneWolf-Aero-Chainguide-3-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Wolf-Tooth-LoneWolf-Aero-Chainguide-3-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Wolf-Tooth-LoneWolf-Aero-Chainguide-3-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Wolf-Tooth-LoneWolf-Aero-Chainguide-3-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Wolf-Tooth-LoneWolf-Aero-Chainguide-3-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Designed specifically for 1x road, gravel, and cyclocross setups, it attaches to your frame’s front derailleur braze-on mount and is compatible with round and oval chainrings from 38-62T. Wolf Tooth also offers clamps for metal bikes with round seat tubes in 28.6, 31.8,<br />and 34.9mm diameters that lack a braze-on mount.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Wolf-Tooth-LoneWolf-Aero-Chainguide-1.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Wolf-Tooth-LoneWolf-Aero-Chainguide-1-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"wolf tooth components LoneWolf aero chain guide for road and gravel bikes shown from behind\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Wolf-Tooth-LoneWolf-Aero-Chainguide-1-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Wolf-Tooth-LoneWolf-Aero-Chainguide-1-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Wolf-Tooth-LoneWolf-Aero-Chainguide-1-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Wolf-Tooth-LoneWolf-Aero-Chainguide-1-768x513.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Wolf-Tooth-LoneWolf-Aero-Chainguide-1-1536x1025.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Wolf-Tooth-LoneWolf-Aero-Chainguide-1-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Wolf-Tooth-LoneWolf-Aero-Chainguide-1.jpg 1810w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Three sizes are offered to fit that spread of chainrings, with up to three bolt positions to combine with the vertical adjustment of the braze-on’s bolt slot allowing you to position the guide 2mm above the chain. Options are:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Low Sweep – 38-52T</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Mid Sweep – 54-58T</li>\n\n\n\n<li>High Sweep – 60-62T</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Wolf-Tooth-LoneWolf-Aero-Chainguide-4.jpg\"><img width=\"2048\" height=\"1366\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Wolf-Tooth-LoneWolf-Aero-Chainguide-4.jpg\" alt=\"parts for wolf tooth components LoneWolf aero chain guide\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Wolf-Tooth-LoneWolf-Aero-Chainguide-4.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Wolf-Tooth-LoneWolf-Aero-Chainguide-4-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Wolf-Tooth-LoneWolf-Aero-Chainguide-4-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Wolf-Tooth-LoneWolf-Aero-Chainguide-4-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Wolf-Tooth-LoneWolf-Aero-Chainguide-4-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Wolf-Tooth-LoneWolf-Aero-Chainguide-4-1536x1025.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Wolf-Tooth-LoneWolf-Aero-Chainguide-4-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>A shim-free adjustment bolt allows inboard/outboard adjustment to position it 2mm off the inside of the chain, with 8mm of total chainline adjustment. A separate bolt controls the angle, letting you rotate the guide to provide maximum “coverage” of the chain.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Wolf-Tooth-LoneWolf-Aero-Chainguide-5.jpg\"><img width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Wolf-Tooth-LoneWolf-Aero-Chainguide-5.jpg\" alt=\"closeup of wolf tooth components LoneWolf aero chain guide\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Wolf-Tooth-LoneWolf-Aero-Chainguide-5.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Wolf-Tooth-LoneWolf-Aero-Chainguide-5-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Wolf-Tooth-LoneWolf-Aero-Chainguide-5-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Wolf-Tooth-LoneWolf-Aero-Chainguide-5-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Wolf-Tooth-LoneWolf-Aero-Chainguide-5-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Wolf-Tooth-LoneWolf-Aero-Chainguide-5-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Wolf-Tooth-LoneWolf-Aero-Chainguide-5-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>For Team Jumbo-Visma (and you, if you own a Cervelo P5 or S5), they offer a special version to fit that frame’s unique braze-on mounting position.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Available now direct and at your local bike shop for $39.95, in black only. Claimed weight is 29g to 33g.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.wolftoothcomponents.com/products/lonewolf-aero-chainguide-braze-on-mount\" target=\"_blank\">WolfToothComponents.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wolf-tooth-lonewolf-aero-chainguide-corrals-your-1x-setup/\">Wolf Tooth LoneWolf Aero Chainguide corrals your 1x setup</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"0805524afab6af21251a9e33b68759f7a2fc85ff968c34cfe1a8fe48bc64de57","category":"Cycling"}